tenance window  Incoming and outgoing email messages will be  held  and delivered when Internet connectivity is restored  In the event of an emergency the VMI Mass notification system will continue to operate as expected  Should it be necessary to call 911 please do so from a cell phone if one is available  If a cell phone is not available and you must use a desk phone  please call the Post Police at 7017 instead of directly dialing 911  The announced maintenance window is from 1730 until 1900 hours to allow for any technical issue arising during the equipment replacement  Our expectation is that services will be restored by 1815 hours  As always the maintenance window was chosen with the following considerations  After academic and business hours Evening meal time for Cadets  Support vendor availability Should you have any questions please contact the IT Help Desk at 7643 or email  Help vmi edu      VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 